---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About" description="About Robert Yang — software engineer, math PhD, South Bay.">
  <h1>About</h1>

  <section class="bio">
    <p>
      I'm Robert Yang (杨天一) — a software engineer at Meta, based in the South Bay with my wife
      and two young kids.
    </p>
    <p>
      My path to software engineering is a bit unusual: I came up through competitive mathematics,
      spent six years getting a PhD in Finance at Carnegie Mellon, worked as a researcher at a
      fintech company, and eventually landed here. The common thread is a preference for hard
      problems with quantifiable answers.
    </p>
    <p>
      At Meta, I work on online experimentation — specifically the infrastructure that decides
      whether an ads experiment produced valid, trustworthy results. It's a domain where statistics,
      data pipelines, and product judgment collide, which suits me.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Background</h2>
    <p>
      Before Meta, I was at Theorem Partners building ML infrastructure for loan evaluation —
      credit modeling, feature engineering, and real-time capital deployment APIs. Before that,
      my PhD research at CMU Tepper focused on how persuasive marketing language affects fee
      premiums in financial products, using Unit Investment Trusts as a natural control.
    </p>
    <p>
      I grew up doing competitive math — USAMO qualifier in high school, Putnam top ~150
      nationally in college. That foundation tends to show up in how I work: I reach for
      first principles and quantitative framing even when the problem looks qualitative on
      the surface.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Education</h2>
    <ul class="edu-list">
      <li>
        <span class="edu-degree">PhD, Finance — Minor in Machine Learning</span>
        <span class="edu-school">Carnegie Mellon University, Tepper School of Business, 2014–2020</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="edu-degree">BS Mathematics, BA Economics — Minor in Computer Science</span>
        <span class="edu-school">Brigham Young University, 2010–2014</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Personal</h2>
    <p>
      I live in the South Bay with my wife of 13+ years and our two kids. Outside of work I'm
      into climbing, basketball, and functional programming. I'm a native Mandarin speaker.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section links">
    <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/tianyi-robert-yang-36366235" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn &rarr;</a>
    <a href="https://github.com/yangro622" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub &rarr;</a>
    <a href="mailto:tianyi.robert.yang@gmail.com">Email &rarr;</a>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .bio p,
  .section p {
    color: var(--c-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .section {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .section h2 {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--c-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .edu-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .edu-list li {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2px;
  }

  .edu-degree {
    color: var(--c-text);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .edu-school {
    color: var(--c-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }

  .links {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .links a {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }
</style>
